directory: crates/ctx-context/tests
domain: Integration/behavioral test suite for ctx-context's serve and hook/session subsystems, exercised entirely against an in-memory `FakeEnv` (no real filesystem). Verifies chain resolution order, absent-scaffolding handling, path-escape rejection, hook injection dedup, and CLI/hook session-ledger sharing.
edit_notes:
  - Both files rely on FakeEnv (flat path->bytes BTreeMap, directories implied by key prefixes); seeding must use exact relative paths the code under test will request.
  - Chain traversal order (root rollup, root intent, per-level rollup+intent descending, then leaf .ctx) is asserted in chain_serve.rs and is a contract on serve::chain_for; hook_session.rs separately depends on the same scaffolding convention (.context/ rollups/intents) via its own seeded tree.
  - Session state path convention `.context/.cache/hook-<session_id>.json` is asserted directly in hook_session.rs and must track the session module's real path scheme.
children:
  - chain_serve.rs: covers serve::chain_for/render — traversal order, missing-node markers, path-escape rejection.
  - hook_session.rs: covers hook::run and CLI path-mode dispatch — injection dedup, session ledger sharing, fail-open on corrupt state.
invariants:
  - Absent scaffolding never errors; it yields present==false nodes with a fixed "(absent...)"/"no leaf" body marker.
  - Source files (e.g. *.rs) never appear as chain node ids alongside .context/ scaffolding nodes.
  - Path traversal (.., leading /, empty segments) is rejected with CtxError::PathEscape before any FakeEnv lookup.